{"title_page": "List of Los Angeles Unified School District schools", "text_new": "{{Cleanup|reason=Use of Bare URLs, redlinks, and inconsistency|date=November 2016}}\n[[File:Seal of the Los Angeles Unified School District.svg|thumbnail|LAUSD Logo]]\n\nThis is a list of schools in the [[Los Angeles Unified School District]].<ref>{{cite web|title=School Listings|url=http://achieve.lausd.net/Page/7704|publisher=Los Angeles Unified School District|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref>  The concept of zones is explained on the LAUSD website.<ref>{{cite web|title=About Zones of Choice|url=http://achieve.lausd.net/Page/1888|publisher=Los Angeles Unified School District|accessdate=6 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n==K\u201312 schools==\n'''Zoned schools'''\n*[[Elizabeth Learning Center]] (Only K\u20138 is zoned) ([[Cudahy, California|Cudahy]], opened 1927)\n*[[James A. Foshay Learning Center]] (Only 6\u201312 is zoned; in order to attend Foshay LC for 9\u201312, a student has to have been enrolled as an 8th grader) (Los Angeles, Opened 1924)\n*[[Robert F. Kennedy Community Schools]] (Opened 2010)\n*Vaughn Next Century Learning Center (formerly Vaughn Street Elementary School)\n'''Magnet/alternative schools'''\n*[[Banneker Special Education Center]] (Willowbrook)\n*[[Marlton School]] ([[Los Angeles, California|Los Angeles]], Opened 1968) \u2013 for deaf and hearing-impaired students\n*[[Valley Alternative Magnet School]]  ([[Los Angeles, California|Los Angeles]]) \u2013 currently the only K\u201312 Magnet School in LAUSD.\n\n==4\u201312 schools==\n[[Image:Sherman Oaks Center for Enriched Studies.JPG|thumb|[[Sherman Oaks Center for Enriched Studies]]]]\n;Zoned schools\n* [[Robert F. Kennedy Community Schools]] (Central Los Angeles New Learning Center 1 Middle School/High School) (Opened September 2010<ref>[http://www.laschools.org/project-status/one-project?project_number=55.98046 Project Status], Los Angeles Unified School District, Facilities Services Division</ref>) (On the site of the [[Ambassador Hotel (Los Angeles)|Ambassador Hotel]])\n\n;Magnet schools\n*[[Sherman Oaks Center for Enriched Studies]]\n\n==K\u20138 schools==\n[[Image:Pio Pico School.jpg|thumb|Pio Pico Span School]]\n;Zoned schools\n* Caroldale Learning Community ([[Carson, California|Carson]])\n* Ellen Ochoa Learning Center ([[Cudahy, California|Cudahy]], Opened 2004\n* Hesby Oaks School (Los Angeles, Reopened 2006)\n* Pio Pico Span School (K\u20138)], (formerly Pio Pico Elementary School, Los Angeles, Opened 1987 as a K\u20136 elementary school, expanded to K\u20138 in 1994\u201395)(When Central Region ES 13 [Carson-Gore Academy of Environmental Studies] opened in 2010, Pio Pico was reconfigured into a middle school [http://www.laschools.org/project-status/one-project?project_number=56.40001])\n* Porter Ranch Community School (Los Angeles, Opened 2012)\n* South Region Span K\u20138 1 (Los Angeles, Opened 2011 [http://www.laschools.org/project-status/one-project?project_number=56.40024])\n* Sylmar Leadership Academy (Los Angeles, Opened 2012)\n* Utah Street Span School\n\n===Option schools===\n*[[Academia Semillas del Pueblo]] (K\u20137, Opened 2002)\n<onlyinclude>\n\n==Secondary schools==\n\n===6-12 schools===\n*Horace Mann UCLA Community School (Originally Horace Mann Middle School) (Opened 2019)\n\n===6\u201312 schools===\n[[Image:MSA-6.jpg|thumb|[[Magnolia Science Academy 6 \u2013 Palms]]]]\n;Magnet schools\n*[[International Studies Learning Center]] (New campus opening fall 2019)\n*[[Los Angeles Center for Enriched Studies]]\n*Maywood Center for Enriched Studies (Maywood, Opened 2017) (Newest School in LAUSD)\n*[[Robert Fulton College Preparatory School]] (Opened 2010 [http://www.laschools.org/project-status/one-project?project_number=56.40037])\n;Magnolia Schools\n*[[Magnolia Science Academy 6 \u2013 Palms]] (Opened 2009) (Currently has 6-7 grades)\n\n===7\u201312 schools===\n'''Zoned schools'''\n* [[Eagle Rock High School (Los Angeles)|Eagle Rock High School]] (Los Angeles) (All grades are zoned) (Opened 1927)(Eagles)\n* [[Rancho Dominguez Preparatory School]] ([[Long Beach, California|Long Beach]]), Opened 2011 (All grades are zoned) [http://www.laschools.org/project-status/one-project?project_number=56.40019]) <!--Relieves Banning HS and Carson HS-->\n\n==High schools (grades 9\u201312)==\n\n===Zoned high schools===\n\n[[Image:Arleta High School.JPG|thumb|[[Arleta High School]]]]\n[[Image:FairfaxHigh Dec2006.jpg|thumb|[[Fairfax High School (Los Angeles)|Fairfax High School]]]]\n[[Image:Hamilton High School LAUSD Entrance.jpg|thumb|[[Alexander Hamilton High School (Los Angeles, California)|Hamilton High School]]]]\n[[Image:Frontviewpalihi.jpg|thumb|[[Palisades Charter High School]]]]\n[[Image:Panorama High School.JPG|thumb|[[Panorama High School]]]]\n[[Image:UniversityHSLosAngeles.jpg|thumb|[[University High School (Los Angeles)|University High School]]]]\n[[Image:Venice High School (Los Angeles, small).jpg|thumb|[[Venice High School (Los Angeles)|Venice High School]]]]\n*[[Dr. Maya Angelou Community High School]] (Opened 2011) [https://angelouchs-lausd-ca.schoolloop.com/](Wolfpack)\n*[[Arleta High School]] ([[Los Angeles]], Opened in 2006 [http://www.laschools.org/project-status/one-project?project_number=55.67307])(Mustangs)\n*[[Phineas Banning High School]] [[Wilmington, Los Angeles|Wilmington]], Opened in 1926)(Pilots)\n*[[Bell High School (California)|Bell High School]] ([[Bell, California|Bell]], Opened 1925)(Eagles)\n*[[Belmont High School (Los Angeles, California)|Belmont High School]] (Los Angeles, Opened 1923) (The existing school will become a 6\u201312 school by 2010 [http://www.laschools.org/project-status/one-project?project_number=117])(Sentinels)\n*[[Helen Bernstein High School]] (Opened Fall 2008 [http://www.laschools.org/project-status/one-project?project_number=55.98014])(Dragons)\n*[[Birmingham High School]] (Opened 1952, became a charter school in 2009)(Patriots)\n*[[Canoga Park High School]] (Opened 1915)(