ddle College High School (Los Angeles)|Middle College High School]]\n*[[Northridge Academy High School]], opened 2004<ref>http://www.laschools.org/project-status/one-project?project_number=55.98032</ref>\n*[[Orthopaedic Hospital Medical Magnet High School]]\n*[[Renaissance Academy (Los Angeles)]]\n*[[Vaughn Next Century Learning Center]]<ref>http://www.vaughncharter.com/</ref>\n*[[View Park Preparatory High School|View Park Preparatory Accelerated High School]]\n*[[J. P. Widney High School|J.P. Widney High School]]\n*[[Port of Los Angeles High School]] [http://www.laschools.org/project-status/one-project?project_number=56.41038])</onlyinclude>\n\n==Middle schools (grades 6\u20138)==\n[[Image:Berendo Middle School.jpg|thumb|[[Berendo Middle School]]]]\n[[Image:J Cochran Jr Middle School.jpg|thumb|Johnnie L. Cochran Jr. Middle School (formerly Mt. Vernon Jr. High)]]\n[[Image:Emerson Middle School.jpg|thumb|[[Emerson Middle School (Los Angeles, California)|Emerson Middle School]]]]\n[[Image:King Middle School.jpg|thumb|Thomas Starr King Middle School]]\n[[Image:Liechty Middle School.jpg|thumb|John H. Liechty Middle School]]\n[[Image:Palms Middle School.jpg|thumb|[[Palms Middle School]]]]\n[[Image:WalterReedMSLosAngeles.jpg|thumb|[[Walter Reed Middle School]]]]\n[[Image:D Webster Middle School.jpg|thumb|Daniel Webster Middle School]]\n\n===Zoned middle schools===\n*John Adams Middle School (Los Angeles)(Patriots)\n*[[Audubon Middle School]] (Los Angeles)(Eagles)\n*Hubert Howe Bancroft Middle School (Los Angeles) \u2013 established 1929, contains a Performing Arts Magnet and a STE[+a]M Magnet (Cougars)\n*Belvedere Middle School (East Los Angeles)(Olympians)\n*[[Berendo Middle School]] (Los Angeles)(Crusaders)\n*Dr. Mary McLeod Bethune Middle School (Los Angeles)(Mighty Mustangs)\n*Luther Burbank Middle School (Los Angeles)(Bears)\n*John Burroughs Middle School (Los Angeles)(Bears)\n*Richard E. Byrd Middle School (Los Angeles) (A new campus for Byrd is completed in 2008)(