roject-status/one-project?project_number=55.67307])(Mustangs)\n*[[Phineas Banning High School]] [[Wilmington, Los Angeles|Wilmington]], Opened in 1926)(Pilots)\n*[[Bell High School (California)|Bell High School]] ([[Bell, California|Bell]], Opened 1925)(Eagles)\n*[[Belmont High School (Los Angeles, California)|Belmont High School]] (Los Angeles, Opened 1923) (The existing school will become a 6\u201312 school by 2010 [http://www.laschools.org/project-status/one-project?project_number=117])(Sentinels)\n*[[Helen Bernstein High School]] (Opened Fall 2008 [http://www.laschools.org/project-status/one-project?project_number=55.98014])(Dragons)\n*[[Birmingham High School]] (Opened 1952, became a charter school in 2009)(Patriots)\n*[[Canoga Park High School]] (Opened 1915)(Hunters) \n*[[Carson High School (Los Angeles)|Carson High School]] ([[Carson, California|Carson]], Opened 1963)(Colts)\n*[[Cesar Chavez High School (San Fernando, California)]] Opened 2011 [http://www.laschools.org/project-status/one-project?project_number=56.40032])(Eagles)\n*[[Chatsworth High School]] (Opened 1963)(Chancellors)\n*[[Cleveland High School (Los Angeles, California)|Grover Cleveland High School]] (Opened 1959)(Cavaliers)\n*[[Miguel Contreras Learning Complex]] (Opened 2006 [http://www.laschools.org/project-status/one-project?project_number=55.98039]) (The area around Contreras is zoned to Belmont High School)(Cobras)\n*[[Crenshaw High School]] (Los Angeles, Opened 1968)(Cougars)\n*[[Susan Miller Dorsey High School]] (Los Angeles, Opened 1937 \u2013 Will gain more permanent capacity by 2011 [http://www.laschools.org/project-status/one-project?project_number=56.40020])(Dons/Donnas)\n*[[Mervyn M. Dymally High School]] (Opened 2012)(Challengers)\n*[[East Valley High School (Los Angeles)|East Valley High School]], [[North Hollywood, California]] (Opened in 2006) [http://www.laschools.org/project-status/one-project?project_number=55.98036])(Falcons)\n*[[El Camino Real High School]] (Los Angeles)