{"title_page": "L\u00e9b\u00e9ny", "text_new": "{{short description|Town in Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron, Hungary}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n| settlement_type        = [[List of cities and towns of Hungary|Town]]\n| subdivision_type       = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n| subdivision_name       = {{HUN}}\n| image_shield           = HUN_L\u00e9b\u00e9ny_C\u00edmer.svg\n| image_flag             = Flag of L\u00e9b\u00e9ny.svg\n| timezone               = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| utc_offset             = +1\n| timezone_DST           = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset_DST         = +2\n| official_name          = L\u00e9b\u00e9ny\n| other_name             = {{lang|la|Quadrata / Stailuco}} {{in lang|la}}\n| map                    = [[Image:GyMSMegye.png|center|thumb|275px|Location of Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron county in Hungary]]\n| subdivision_type1      = [[Counties of Hungary|County]]\n| subdivision_name1      = [[Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron County|Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron]]\n| subdivision_type2      = [[Districts of Hungary|District]]\n| subdivision_name2      = [[Mosonmagyar\u00f3v\u00e1r District|Mosonmagyar\u00f3v\u00e1r]]\n| area_total_km2         = 81.36\n| population_total       = 3232\n| population_as_of       = 2015\n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| population_footnotes   = <ref name=\"HunStat2015\">''[http://www.ksh.hu/apps/shop.kiadvany?p_kiadvany_id=81322&p_temakor_kod=KSH&p_session_id=800051036609396&p_lang=EN Gazetteer of Hungary, 1st January 2015]''. Hungarian Central Statistical Office.</ref>\n| postal_code_type       = [[Postal codes in Hungary|Postal code]]\n| postal_code            = 9155\n| area_code_type         = [[Telephone numbers in Hungary|Area code]]\n| area_code              = (+36) 96\n| blank_name             = Motorways\n| blank_info             = [[M1 motorway (Hungary)|M1]]\n| blank2_name            = Distance from Budapest\n| blank2_info            = {{convert|145|km|abbr=on}} East\n| website                = {{URL|https://lebeny.hu/}}\n}}\n\n'''L\u00e9b\u00e9ny''' is a town in [[Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron]] County, midway between Mosonmagyar\u00f3v\u00e1r and Gy\u0151r, [[Hungary]]. It has a [[Romanesque architecture|Romanesque]] monastic church commenced in 1208. Similar family or clan-financed medieval Hungarian monastic churches can be found in [[J\u00e1k]], [[\u00d3csa]], [[Ny\u00edrb\u00e1tor]], [[Harina]] and [[Laslea|M\u0103l\u00e2ncrav]].\n[[Image:Szent Jakab templom, Lebeny2.jpg|240px|right|thumb|The [[Romanesque architecture|Romanesque]] church]]\n[[Image:L\u00e9b\u00e9ny - WWI memorial.JPG|right|thumb|240px|First world war memorial]]\n\n==Early history==\nThe L\u00e9b\u00e9ny area has been occupied continuously since prehistoric times. Signs of human occupation have been found from the Neolithic, through the Bronze and Iron Ages, including excavated remains of [[Celts|Celtic habitation]]. When [[Tiberius]], later the Roman Emperor, overran [[Transdanubia]] in AD 9, he established a military camp and civilian settlement in the area of present-day L\u00e9b\u00e9ny.\n\nIn later centuries the region was inhabited by [[Huns]], then by [[Lombards]], and then by [[Pannonian Avars|Avars]], who were converted to Christianity. Excavations have confirmed there was already a sizeable community at L\u00e9b\u00e9ny at the time of the [[Hungarian Conquest of the Carpathian Basin]] in the 9th and 10th centuries, including Slavic groups.\n\nThe first written mention of the place was under the name Libin in 1208.<ref>The section summarizes the Hungarian Wikipedia article on L\u00e9b\u00e9ny. [[:hu:L\u00e9b\u00e9ny|Retrieved 2 December 2017.]]</ref>\n\n==Romanesque church==\nNow the parish church of St James the Apostle, this Romanesque church was originally built for a community of [[Benedictine]] monks. Its nave with two aisles and three apses forms a [[basilica]] structure. The capitals of the columns inside the church are carved with plant ornamentation.\n\n==Further detail==\n*Photograph of the church with an extended historical caption: [http://www.trekearth.com/gallery/Europe/Hungary/West/Gyor-Moson-Sopron/Lebeny/photo1145367.htm Retrieved 31 August 2017.]\n*Ger\u0151 L\u00e1szl\u00f3 (1984): ''Magyar m\u0171eml\u00e9ki ABC'' (ABC of Hungarian Historical Monuments). In Hungarian\n*Gervers-Moln\u00e1r Vera (1972): A k\u00f6z\u00e9pkori Magyarorsz\u00e1g rotund\u00e1i (Rotundas of Medieval Hungary). In Hungarian\n*Henszlmann Imre (1876): ''Magyarorsz\u00e1g \u00f3-kereszty\u00e9n, rom\u00e1n \u00e9s \u00e1tmeneti styl\u00fc m\u0171-eml\u00e9keinek r\u00f6vid ismertet\u00e9se'' (Short Survey of Hungary's Early Christian, Romanesque, and Transitional Style Historic Monuments). In Hungarian\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|L\u00e9b\u00e9ny}}\n* {{Official website|https://lebeny.hu/}} in Hungarian and German\n\n{{Mosonmagyar\u00f3v\u00e1r District}}\n{{Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lebeny}}\n[[Category:Populated places in Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron County]]\n[[Category:Romanesque architecture in Hungary]]\n\n\n{{Gyor-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Town in Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron, Hungary}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n| settlement_type        = [[List of cities and towns of Hungary|Town]]\n| subdivision_type       = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n| subdivision_name       = {{HUN}}\n| image_shield           = HUN_L\u00e9b\u00e9ny_C\u00edmer.svg\n| image_flag             = Flag of L\u00e9b\u00e9ny.svg\n| timezone               = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| utc_offset             = +1\n| timezone_DST           = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset_DST         = +2\n| official_name          = L\u00e9b\u00e9ny\n| other_name             = {{lang|la|Quadrata / Stailuco}} {{in lang|la}}\n| map                    = [[Image:GyMSMegye.png|center|thumb|275px|Location of Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron county in Hungary]]\n| subdivision_type1      = [[Counties of Hungary|County]]\n| subdivision_name1      = [[Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron County|Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron]]\n| subdivision_type2      = [[Districts of Hungary|District]]\n| subdivision_name2      = [[Mosonmagyar\u00f3v\u00e1r District|Mosonmagyar\u00f3v\u00e1r]]\n| area_total_km2         = 81.36\n| population_total       = 3232\n| population_as_of       = 2015\n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| population_footnotes   = <ref name=\"HunStat2015\">''[http://www.ksh.hu/apps/shop.kiadvany?p_kiadvany_id=81322&p_temakor_kod=KSH&p_session_id=800051036609396&p_lang=EN Gazetteer of Hungary, 1st January 2015]''. Hungarian Central Statistical Office.</ref>\n| postal_code_type       = [[Postal codes in Hungary|Postal code]]\n| postal_code            = 9155\n| area_code_type         = [[Telephone numbers in Hungary|Area code]]\n| area_code              = (+36) 96\n| blank_name             = Motorways\n| blank_info             = [[M1 motorway (Hungary)|M1]]\n| blank2_name            = Distance from Budapest\n| blank2_info            = {{convert|145|km|abbr=on}} East\n| website                = {{URL|https://lebeny.hu/}}\n}}\n\n'''L\u00e9b\u00e9ny''' is a town in [[Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron]] County, midway between Mosonmagyar\u00f3v\u00e1r and Gy\u0151r, [[Hungary]]. It has a [[Romanesque architecture|Romanesque]] monastic church commenced in 1208. Similar family or clan-financed medieval Hungarian monastic churches can be found in [[J\u00e1k]], [[\u00d3csa]], [[Ny\u00edrb\u00e1tor]], [[Harina]] and [[Laslea|M\u0103l\u00e2ncrav]].\n[[Image:Szent Jakab templom, Lebeny2.jpg|240px|right|thumb|The [[Romanesque architecture|Romanesque]] church]]\n[[Image:L\u00e9b\u00e9ny - WWI memorial.JPG|right|thumb|240px|First world war memorial]]\n\n==Early history==\nThe L\u00e9b\u00e9ny area has been occupied continuously since prehistoric times. Signs of human occupation have been found from the Neolithic, through the Bronze and Iron Ages, including excavated remains of [[Celts|Celtic habitation]]. When [[Tiberius]], later the Roman Emperor, overran [[Transdanubia]] in AD 9, he established a military camp and civilian settlement in the area of present-day L\u00e9b\u00e9ny.\n\nIn later centuries the region was inhabited by [[Huns]], then by [[Lombards]], and then by [[Pannonian Avars|Avars]], who were converted to Christianity. Excavations have confirmed there was already a sizeable community at L\u00e9b\u00e9ny at the time of the [[Hungarian Conquest of the Carpathian Basin]] in the 9th and 10th centuries, including Slavic groups.\n\nThe first written mention of the place was under the name Libin in 1208.<ref>The section summarizes the Hungarian Wikipedia article on L\u00e9b\u00e9ny. [[:hu:L\u00e9b\u00e9ny|Retrieved 2 December 2017.]]</ref>\n\n==Romanesque church==\nNow the parish church of St James the Apostle, this Romanesque church was originally built for a community of [[Benedictine]] monks. Its nave with two aisles and three apses forms a [[basilica]] structure. The capitals of the columns inside the church are carved with plant ornamentation.\n\n==Further detail==\n*Photograph of the church with an extended historical caption: [http://www.trekearth.com/gallery/Europe/Hungary/West/Gyor-Moson-Sopron/Lebeny/photo1145367.htm Retrieved 31 August 2017.]\n*Ger\u0151 L\u00e1szl\u00f3 (1984): ''Magyar m\u0171eml\u00e9ki ABC'' (ABC of Hungarian Historical Monuments). In Hungarian\n*Gervers-Moln\u00e1r Vera (1972): A k\u00f6z\u00e9pkori Magyarorsz\u00e1g rotund\u00e1i (Rotundas of Medieval Hungary). In Hungarian\n*Henszlmann Imre (1876): ''Magyarorsz\u00e1g \u00f3-kereszty\u00e9n, rom\u00e1n \u00e9s \u00e1tmeneti styl\u00fc m\u0171-eml\u00e9keinek r\u00f6vid ismertet\u00e9se'' (Short Survey of Hungary's Early Christian, Romanesque, and Transitional Style Historic Monuments). In Hungarian\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|L\u00e9b\u00e9ny}}\n* {{Official website|https://lebeny.hu/}} in Hungarian and German\n\n{{Mosonmagyar\u00f3v\u00e1r District}}\n{{Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lebeny}}\n[[Category:Populated places in Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron County]]\n[[Category:Romanesque architecture in Hungary]]\n\n\n{{Gyor-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/L%C3%A9b%C3%A9ny"}
